I"<h3 id="control-at-device-level">Control at device level</h3>
<ol>
  <li>login to tenda : http://192.168.0.1/index.html</li>
  <li>Enter your login and password (password is behind the device)</li>
  <li>go to parental control tab</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/tenda-parental-control.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<h3 id="settings-for-device">Settings for Device</h3>
<ol>
  <li>set the timing for the device</li>
  <li>select blacklist</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/tenda-device-control.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<h3 id="using-opendns">Using OpenDNS</h3>
<p>Using open DNS you can change these settings for the router itself. 
So after this any device connected to this router will not be able to access
unwanted websites and net will be safe and secure.</p>

<p><a href="https://welcome.opendns.com/">OpenDNS</a></p>

<p><img src="/images/tenda-opendns.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<p>OpenDNS IP Addresses are mentioned in the url at the bottom. You can also test 
by clicking on URL that opendns is being used by your router.</p>

<p><img src="/images/opendns-check.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

